# Invert Binary Tree

## Problem

Given the root of a binary tree, invert the tree and return its root.

Inverting a tree means swapping the left and right child of every node in the tree.

---

## Concept

This problem is based on **recursion**.

At each node:

* Swap its left and right children
* Then recursively apply the same process to both sides

---

## Approach

* If root is null → return null
* Swap left and right subtree
* Recursively invert left and right
* Return the root

---

## Code (Java)

```java id="jv9x2k"
class Solution {
    public TreeNode invertTree(TreeNode root) {
        if(root == null)
        {
            return root;
        }

        TreeNode temp = root.left;
        root.left = invertTree(root.right);
        root.right = invertTree(temp);
        return root;
    }
}
```

---

## Time Complexity

* O(n) → visit each node once

## Space Complexity

* O(h) → recursion stack (h = height of tree)

---

## Mistakes / Learnings

* Don’t forget base case (root == null)
* Always store one child before swapping (use temp)
* Recursion handles entire tree automatically
